%TOC%

---++ Long-distance calls

Please use a Call-by-Call prefix when making long-distance calls, as this is much cheaper than dialling directly.  A list of providers is available at http://www.billiger-telefonieren.de/.  Note that some of these are blacklisted by HRZ for giving false billing information; you can see the list at http://www.hrz.tu-darmstadt.de/persoenlicher_arbeitsplatz/telefon/sprachdienste/callbycall/index.de.jsp.

Long-distance calls should be made for work-related purposes only.  You need to use a calling card to make personal long-distance calls.  The attached files indicate where to buy calling cards and how to use them.

---++ Restricted phone numbers

It is not possible to dial premium (0900) numbers directly from the office phones.  However, some embassies require visa applicants to call such numbers.  In such cases, seek advance permission of IG.  If she agrees to the call, then you can dial 99 to reach the university switchboard, explain the situation, and have them dial the number for you.

---++ Touch-tone (DTMF)

Automated answering systems and teleconferencing systems will often ask you to input data via the telephone keypad ("Press 1 for support, press 2 for sales, Â…", "Enter your teleconference PIN now", etc.).  Our office telephones by default will _not_ send the touch tones (also known as DTMF signals, or _Tonwahl_ or _MFV_ in German) when the keys are pressed.  To enable touch tone for a call, dial <b>0*</b> as soon as the connection is made.  The telephone display will show "MFV" to confirm that touch-tone mode has been activated.

---++ Telephone directory (call display)

For internal calls the office phones display the name and number of the calling party.  If you notice an incorrect entry, please report it to Telefon AG by dialling 3100.

---++ Teleconferencing

See TelefonKonferenz for detailed instructions.

---++ Telephone manuals

If you have trouble identifying the model of your telephone, try looking on the back or bottom of the unit for the model number.

